{{Infobox protected area | name = Battle of Sakarya National Historic Park | alt_name = ''Sakarya Meydan Muharebesi Tarihi Milli Parkı'' | iucn_category = | photo = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | photo_width = | map = | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | relief = | label = | label_position = | mark = | marker_size = | location = [[Ankara]], Turkey | nearest_city = | coords = | coords_ref = | area = | designation = | authorized = | created = | established = {{start date|2015|2|8}} | designated = | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | visitation_ref = | governing_body = [[Ministry of Forest and Water Management (Turkey)|Ministry of Forest and Water Management]] | administrator = | operator = | owner = | world_heritage_site = | website = [http://www.milliparklar.gov.tr/AnaSayfa/resimliHaber/15-02-09/SAKARYA_MEYDAN_MUHAREBES%C4%B0_TAR%C4%B0H%C4%B0_M%C4%B0LL%C4%B0_PARKI_KURULDU.aspx?sflang=tr www.milliparklar.gov.tr/mp/sakaryameydanmuharebesi/index.htm] | child = | embedded = }} '''Battle of Sakarya National Historic Park''' ({{lang-tr|Sakarya Meydan Muharebesi Tarihi Milli Parkı}}), established on February 8, 2015, is a [[protected area]] of national historic significance associated with the [[Turkish War of Independence]] ({{lang-tr|İstiklâl Savaşı}}) comprising the battleground of the [[Battle of Sakarya]] ({{lang-tr|Sakarya Meydan Muharebesi}}) in the [[Greco-Turkish War (1919–22)]]. It is located in the [[Polatlı]] and [[Haymana]] districts of [[Ankara Province]].<ref name="mp"/>
