{{distinguish|Herschel Island (Canada)}}
{{Infobox Island | name =Herschel Island | image= PNCabodeHornos.JPG | image_caption = Island landscape, the interior of the [[Cabo de Hornos National Park]] | location = [[Pacific Ocean]], [[Atlantic Ocean]] | country = Chile | coordinates = {{coord|55.845|S|67.2953|W|display=inline,title}} }}
'''Herschel Island''' is an island belonging to [[Chile]]. The island is located just north of the [[Drake Passage]] and southeast of [[Tierra del Fuego]]. It is part of the [[Hermite Islands]].<ref>{{cite book|language=es|first1=R. F.|last1=Rozzi|first2 = A. | last2 = Massardo | first3 = C.B.| last3 = Berghöfer | first4 = A. | last4 = Anderson | first5 = M | last5 = Mansilla | first6 = J. | last6 = Mansilla | first7 = U. | last7 = Plana | first8 = P. | last8 = Berghöfer | first9 = P. | last9 = Araya | first10 = E. | last10 = Barros|title=Reserva de Biosfera Cabo de Hornos: Documento de Base para la Incorporación del Territorio Insular del Cabo de Hornos a la Red Mundial de Reservas de Biosfera.|year=2006|publisher=Ediciones de la Universidad de Magallanes|location=Punta Arenas}}</ref> The Franklin Channel on the north side of the island separates Herschel from the southernmost [[Wollaston Islands]]. Herschel Island is part of the [[Cabo de Hornos National Park]].
It is one of the southernmost landforms in the Americas ([[Hornos Island]] is further south). The island was named in honor of the British astronomer [[John Herschel]].<ref>[http://dicci-eponimos.blogspot.com/2010/01/herschel-john.html ''Diccionario de Epónimos''. Herschel (John)]</ref>
