{{main|ISO 3166-2}}

'''ISO 3166-2:RU''' is the entry for [[Russia]] in [[ISO 3166-2]], part of the [[ISO 3166]] [[standardization|standard]] published by the [[International Organization for Standardization]] (ISO), which defines [[code]]s for some of the names of the principal [[country subdivision|subdivision]]s (e.g., [[province]]s or [[state (administrative division)|state]]s) of all [[country|countries]] coded in [[ISO 3166-1]]. ISO 3166-2:RU contains no codes for the Russian-administered [[Republic of Crimea]] and [[Sevastopol|Federal City of Sevastopol]], which are internationally recognized as part of Ukraine and do have codes in [[ISO 3166-2:UA|Ukraine's entry in ISO 3166-2]].

Currently for Russia, ISO 3166-2 codes are defined for the following [[federal subjects of Russia|federal subjects]]:
* [[republics of Russia|21 republics]]
* [[krais of Russia|9 administrative territories]]
* [[oblasts of Russia|46 administrative regions]]
* [[federal cities of Russia|2 autonomous cities]]
* [[autonomous oblasts of Russia|1 autonomous region]]
* [[autonomous okrugs of Russia|4 autonomous districts]]

Each code consists of two parts, separated by a hyphen. The first part is {{mono|RU}}, the [[ISO 3166-1 alpha-2]] code of Russia. The second part is either of the following:
* two letters: republics
* three letters: all other subdivisions

==Current codes==
Subdivision names are listed as in the ISO 3166-2 standard published by the ISO 3166 Maintenance Agency (ISO 3166/MA).
* Subdivision name 1 &mdash; Romanization system: [[BGN/PCGN romanization of Russian|BGN/PCGN]] 1947
* Subdivision name 2 &mdash; Romanization system: [[GOST 16876-71|GOST]] 1983

