{{unreferenced|date=March 2015}} {{coord|29|50|N|19|45|E|display=title}} {{Location map|Libya | caption = Location of Sabkhat Ghuzayyil | lon_deg = 19 | lon_min = 45 | lon_dir = E | lat_deg = 29 | lat_min = 50 | lat_dir = N }}
'''Sabkhat Ghuzayyil''' is [[Libya]]'s lowest point at 47 meters (154 feet) below sea level, and is just southeast of the [[Gulf of Sidra]]. It is located in the [[Al Wahat District]] of the [[Cyrenaica]] region in northeastern Libya.
The area is dry today but in the [[Holocene Wet Phase]] it was flooded.
[[Ajdabiya]] is the main city in the area which is located just northeast of the coastal areas below sea level. [[Brega]] is a smaller city located more westerly near the shore and is wedged between the sea and these low-lying lands.
[[Category:Geography of Libya]] [[Category:Al Wahat District]] [[Category:Lowest points]]
