{{Location map | Antarctica | lat_deg = 79 | lat_min = 29 | lat_dir = S | lon_deg = 85 | lon_min = 37 | lon_dir = W | mark = | marksize = 12 | AlternativeMap = Antarctica relief location map.jpg | label = White Escarpment | position = top | caption = Location of White Escarpment, [[Ellsworth Land]], [[Antarctica]] }}
'''White Escarpment''' is an escarpment in the west part of the [[Heritage Range]], extending for 15&nbsp;nautical miles (28&nbsp;km) between the heads of the [[Splettstoesser Glacier|Splettstoesser]] and [[Dobbratz Glacier]]s. Named by the [[University of Minnesota]] Geological Party to these mountains, 1963–64, for Chief Warrant Officer Ronald B. White, pilot with the 62nd Transportation Detachment, who assisted the party.
